{{Lunisolar September}} '''September 14''' is the 14th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events ==
* {{ill|Bunkyū (era)|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1863|ja|1863rd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – Japan’s first English-language daily newspaper, *The Daily Japan Herald*, is launched in Yokohama.
* {{ill|Meiji (era)|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Shō Tai|ja|尚泰|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , King of {{ill|Ryukyu Kingdom|ja|琉球王国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , is officially designated as the "Ryukyu Domain King" and Ranked among the {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Japanese nobility).
== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenpō (era)|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11 (Gregorian {{ill|1840|ja|1840th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 9|ja|10月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Matsumoto Fūko|ja|松本楓湖|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a Japanese {{ill|painter|ja|Painter|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (+ {{ill|1923|ja|1923rd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenryaku (era)|ja|天暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8 ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|954|ja|954th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 13|ja|10月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Imperial Prince Shigeaki|ja|重明親王|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the fourth son of {{ill|Emperor Daigo|ja|醍醐天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|906|ja|906年|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Manju (era)|ja|万寿|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4 (Julian {{ill|1027|ja|1027th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Fujiwara no Genshi|ja|藤原妍子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Empress Chūgū|ja|中宮|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} of {{ill|Emperor Sanjō|ja|三条天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and daughter of {{ill|Fujiwara no Michinaga|ja|Fujiwara no Michinaga|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|994|ja|994th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Ōei (era)|ja|Ōei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12 (Julian {{ill|1405|ja|1405th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 7|ja|10月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Date Masamune (Dai Zen Daibu)|ja|伊達政宗 (大膳大夫)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a Japanese {{ill|samurai|ja|武将|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1353|ja|1353rd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Kan'ei (era)|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 20 (Gregorian {{ill|1643|ja|1643rd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Kasuga no Tsubone|ja|春日局|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , the wet nurse of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1579|ja|1579th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Enpō (era)|ja|延宝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6 (Gregorian {{ill|1678|ja|1678th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 29|ja|10月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunashige|ja|徳川綱重|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , Lord of {{ill|Kōfu Domain|ja|甲府藩|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , third son of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemitsu|ja|徳川家光|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , and father of {{ill|Tokugawa Ienobu|ja|徳川家宣|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1644|ja|1644th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
* {{ill|Ansei (era)|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6 (Gregorian {{ill|1859|ja|1859th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|October 9|ja|10月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Umeda Unpin|ja|梅田雲浜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a {{ill|Confucian scholar|ja|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|儒学者|zh|儒生|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1815|ja|1815th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
