* {{ill|Bunkyū (era)|ja|文久|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|1863|ja|1863rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – Japan’s first English-language daily newspaper, *The Daily Japan Herald*, is launched in Yokohama.
* {{ill|Meiji (era)|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 5 (Gregorian {{ill|1872|ja|1872nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Shō Tai|ja|尚泰|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , King of {{ill|Ryukyu Kingdom|ja|琉球王国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , is officially designated as the "Ryukyu Domain King" and Ranked among the {{ill|Kazoku|ja|華族|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Japanese nobility).
== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenpō (era)|ja|天保|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 11 (Gregorian {{ill|1840|ja|1840th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|October 9|ja|10月9日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ) – {{ill|Matsumoto Fūko|ja|松本楓湖|qq=draft|qq=draft}} , a Japanese {{ill|painter|ja|Painter|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (+ {{ill|1923|ja|1923rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ).
